    "source_type": "blog_analysis",
    "title": "Quoting Georgi Gerganov",
    "summary": "<blockquote cite=\"https://twitter.com/ggerganov/status/2038674698809102599\"><p>Note that the main issues that people currently unknowingly face with local models mostly revolve around the harness and some intricacies around model chat templates and prompt construction. Sometimes there are even pure inference bugs. From typing the task in the client to the actual result, there is a long chain of components that atm are not only fragile - are also developed by different parties. So it's difficult to consolidate the entire stack and you have to keep in mind that what you are currently observing is with very high probability still broken in some subtle way along that chain.</p></blockquote> <p class=\"cite\">&mdash; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ggerganov/status/2038674698809102599\">Georgi Ger...",
